Mercury was the Roman divinity of commerce and gain, and presided, of course, over merchantS, markets‚ etc. Hence the estab- lishment of a guild of traders is here connected with the dedication of his temple. His festival was celebrated, chiefly by merchants, on the Ides of May, the day when his temple was consecrated. By annona is properly meant the yearly produce derived from anything, particularly from the main article of trade, namely‚ grain. From this original sense comes the meaning of “the mai-ket price‚” as it rose or fell, “ the market‚’' as in the present instance, etc. Under the re- public, a praefectus annonae, or prefect of provisionS‚ especially of the corn market, was only appointed in times of extraordinary scarcity.
